@xiejw Thanks, that makes complete sense. I'm now confused though as to why the test does not produce an error on my local. I did a bazel clean before trying it again and it still passes even though six is not imported. This is the command I'm using:

bazel test --config=opt //tensorflow/python/estimator:pandas_io_test

I've also used

bazel run --config=opt //tensorflow/python/estimator:pandas_io_test

It says 17 passing.

Should I be running the tests in a different way for local development?
